    {
      "text": "Kalavinka (迦陵頻伽) is a celestial creature in Buddhism, said to be dwelling in Sukhavati (Western Pureland of Amitabha Buddha). \nKalavinka has a human head and bird torso.\n\nI think the dancers did a great job portraying it. Love the bird chirping sounds in the background too. 💖",
      "platform": "YouTube",
      "url": "https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bgGqgjkBLek",
      "likes": 1787,
      "lang": "en"
    },
    {
      "text": "It's an evidence of coexistence of two greatest civilizations- China and India. Can't we stop fighting over nothing and just appreciate this.",
